      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Cook the dates",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Put the {{dried-dates}} in a small saucepan with 175 ml of water. Bring to a simmer and cook for 4 minutes until very soft. Remove from the heat, stir in the {{bicarbonate-of-soda}} (it will foam briefly) and leave to cool for 10 minutes.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make the sponge",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Heat the oven to 170°C fan. Grease and line a 20×30 cm tin. Beat the {{unsalted-butter}} (for the sponge) and {{light-brown-sugar}} together until pale. Beat in the {{free-range-eggs}} and {{vanilla-extract}}. Fold in the {{plain-flour}} and {{baking-powder}}. Stir in the cooked date mixture. Pour into the tin.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Bake, 25 to 30 minutes",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Bake for 25 to 30 minutes until a skewer comes out clean. While it bakes, make the sauce.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make the toffee sauce",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Melt the {{unsalted-butter}} (for the sauce) and {{dark-brown-sugar}} in a saucepan over medium heat, stirring. Add the {{double-cream}} and {{fine-sea-salt}}. Simmer for 3 to 4 minutes until the ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "toffee sauce",
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termId": "cmpaehv380000skv48x6c9dpo"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "text": " is glossy and coats a spoon.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Soak and serve",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "As soon as the sponge comes out of the oven, pour two-thirds of the sauce over the top and leave for 10 minutes to soak in. Cut into squares and serve with the remaining sauce alongside.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
